Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 170 Pacific Highway, St Leonards. Situated just 
moments from St Leonards Station and Crows Nest town centre, this trophy freehold building comprises five-storeys of newly refurbished offices. Currently fully leased with a long WALE of 4+ years, 170 Pacific Highway is also DA approved for an additional two storeys of office space. Accordingly, the property is a secure investment with significant value-add potential, further capitalising from its location within a rapidly growing commercial precinct. 

170 Pacific Highway benefits from the following key attributes:

- Net income: $2,699,017 per annum*
- 100% leased with WALE of 4+ years
- NLA of 4,402sqm* plus 116 car spaces
- Five-storey freehold office building sitting on huge 2,434sqm* land parcel
- Over $2,600,000 CAPEX invested since 2015
- DA approved for an additional two storeys (NLA 1,670sqm*)
- Views of Sydney CBD and Sydney Harbour
- Set to benefit from future developments within the St Leonards/Crows Nest priority precinct
- Easy walk to St Leonards Station and Royal North Shore Hospital
- 4-Star NABERS Energy rating

Interested parties are invited to submit their expressions of interest for the purchase of 170 Pacific Highway, St Leonards by Wednesday, 1 July 2020 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate
Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Within the St Leonards 2036 Final Plan

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present 92 Chandos Street, St Leonards.  Situated just metres from Crows Nest Village and a short walk to St Leonards Station and the future Metro, 92 Chandos Street is a fully leased newly refurbished, three-storey commercial freehold building.  In an elevated position, 92 Chandos Street enjoys a north facing aspect with district views over  Naremburn. On the ground floor, the main entrance is off Chandos Street with the secure car park with parking for  12 cars accessed off Henry Lane. The tenant has recently undergone a significant fitout to the building providing a high end, modern office space.  This blue-chip investment is 100% fully leased to long standing, award winning tenant, Strata Choice, on a 3+3 year lease.

92 Chandos Street, St Leonards benefits from the following key attributes:
- Net Income: $359,074.74 per annum* with desirable lease terms
- Building area of 638sqm* with dual street frontages and 12 secure car spaces accessed from the rear lane
- Newly refurbished three storey freehold commercial building with development upside (STCA)
- 100% leased to long standing award winning tenant, Strata Choice, on a 3+3 year lease
- Set to benefit from the rapid growth of the St Leonards and Crows Nest 2036  Final Plan
- Situated metres from Crows Nest Village, St Leonards station and future Crows Nest Metro Station
- Future development upside under the St Leonards & Crows Nest 2036 Final Plan (STCA)
- Benefiting from no car parking levies

*Approximate
